  <h1>
   draw_set_colour
  </h1>
  With this function you can set the base draw colour for the game.
  
  
   This will affect drawing of fonts, forms, primitives and 3D, however it will not affect sprites (drawn
  <a href="../Sprites_And_Tiles/draw_sprite.htm">
   manually
  </a>
  or by an instance). If any affected graphics are drawn with their own colour values, this value will be ignored.
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">draw_set_colour(col);
</code></pre>
  <table>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
     <th>
      Argument
     </th>
     <th>
      Type
     </th>
     <th>
      Description
     </th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      col
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Reference/Drawing/Colour_And_Alpha/Colour_And_Alpha.htm">
        Colour
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The colour to set for drawing.
     </td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
  </table>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">N/A
</code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">draw_set_alpha(0.5);
draw_set_colour(c_black);
draw_text(x+5, y+5, "LEVEL 1");
draw_set_alpha(1);
draw_set_colour(c_white);
draw_text(x, y, "LEVEL 1");
</code></pre>
  The above code will draw some text at the specified position with a shadow effect created by modified draw alpha and colour.
 </body>
